The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Bengal teams for the Moin-ud Dowlah Gold Cup in Hyderabad and the JP Atray meet in Chandigarh will be selected on Friday.      
	Two separate teams are set to be picked from among the 40 probables. While Laxmi Ratan Shukla is almost certain to lead one team, Ranadeb Bose was well placed to get the skippers job for the other side. Coach Roger Binny will be present at the meeting.      
	Meanwhile, Kanti Ganguly, sports minister of the state, met the Cricket Association of Bengal officials on Thursday. The minister has requested the CAB to support the initiative to take over the Calcutta Racecourse for setting up a sports complex.          
	 Camelia Group defeated SAI, Kolkata 4-2 in the Bengal Premier League table tennis championship held at the SAI, Eastern Complex on Thursday. Calcutta Riverside were held 3-3 by Chirag United at Chandannagar.                
	SOCCER: IFA Shield  Mohun Bagan vs George Telegraph at the Mohun Bagan ground Churchill Brothers vs Lajong FC at the Barasat Stadium. Both from 3pm.                                                                                                                                                                       
